OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1782301688
OL,3,CDrivers risk #110 fines for trying to
OL,4,Ckeep cool in stationary cars with air
OL,5,Ccon
OL,7,FDrivers seeking to cool down by
OL,8,Fsitting in stationary cars with the
OL,9,Fair conditioning on are being warned
OL,10,Fthey could be fined under emissions
OL,11,Flaws.
OL,13,FThe RAC said remaining in a vehicle
OL,14,Fwith its engine idling causes air
OL,15,Fpollution.
OL,17,FThe standard fine is #40 if caught by
OL,18,Fa police officer or #80 from a civil
OL,19,Fenforcement officer.
OL,21,FBoth are halved if paid quickly.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
